 metropolitan area|Louisville-Jefferson County]]*<ref>The 2010 Census population for the part within the South (Kentucky) is 973,271.</ref>\n| [[Kentucky|KY]]-[[Indiana|IN]]\n| align=right | 1,297,310\n| align=center | 45\n|-\n|}\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki> Asterisk indicates part of the metropolitan area is outside the states classified as Southern.\n\n==Major combined statistical areas==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! valign=bottom | Rank\n! valign=bottom | Combined Statistical Area\n! valign=bottom | State(s)\n! valign=bottom | Population (2017 est.) <ref>{{cite web |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/PEP/2017/GCTPEPANNR.US41PR |title=Annual Estimates of the Resident Population: April 1, 2010 to July 1, 2017 - United States -- Combined Statistical Area; and for Puerto Rico |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]], Population Division |date=March 2018 |accessdate=March 31, 2018 }}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n|-\n| align=center | 1\n| [[Baltimore-Washington metropolitan area|Washington-Baltimore-Arlington]]\n| [[District of Columbia|DC]]-[[Maryland|MD]]-[[Virginia|VA]]-[[West Virginia|WV]]-[[Pennsylvania|PA]]\n| align=right| 9,764,315\n|-\n| align=center | 2\n| [[Dallas-Fort Worth metroplex|Dallas-Fort Worth]]\n| [[Texas|TX]]\n| align=right| 7,846,293\n|-\n| align=center | 3\n| [[Greater Houston|Houston-The Woodlands-Baytown]]\n| [[Texas|TX]]\n| align=right | 7,093,190\n|-\n| align=center | 4\n| [[Miami metropolitan area#Combined Statistical Area|Miami-Fort Lauderdale-Port St. Lucie]]\n| [[Florida|FL]]\n| align=right| 6,828,241\n|-\n| align=center | 5\n| [[Atlanta metropolitan area|Atlanta-Athens-Clarke County-Sandy Springs]]\n| [[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n| align=right | 6,555,956\n|-\n| align=center | 6\n| [[Greater Orlando|Orlando-Deltona-Daytona Beach]]\n| [[Florida|FL]]\n| align=right | 3,284,198\n|-\n| align=center | 7\n| [[Charlotte metropolitan area|Charlotte-Concord]]\n| [[North C